  "prompt": "If I were to watch my last movie, which movie would you recommend?",
  "response": "If I were to recommend a movie that could serve as a profound and meaningful \"last movie\" experience, I\u2019d suggest **\"The Tree of Life\" (2011)**, directed by Terrence Malick. This film is a meditative exploration of life, existence, memory, and the connections between the microcosm of human experience and the vastness of the universe. Its poetic storytelling and stunning visuals make it a deeply reflective and emotional journey.\n\nAlternatively, if you\u2019re looking for something more uplifting yet thought-provoking, **\"The Secret Life of Walter Mitty\" (2013)** could be a beautiful choice. It\u2019s a celebration of life, adventure, and embracing the present moment.\n\nFor a classic, **\"It\u2019s a Wonderful Life\" (1946)** is a timeless story about the impact one life can have on others, filled with warmth and hope.\n\nUltimately, the best choice depends on your personal tastes and what kind of emotional or philosophical experience you\u2019re seeking in your \"last movie.\" Let me know your preferences, and I can refine the recommendation further!",
